  <title translate="true">sample variance</title>
  <body>
    <para styleclass="Normal"><text style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt; color:#000000;" translate="true">A</text><text style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt; font-style:italic; color:#000000;" translate="true">&#32;</text><text style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt; font-weight:bold; color:#000000;" translate="true">sample variance</text><text style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt; color:#000000;" translate="true"> is the sum of squared deviations from the mean of two or more samples from the same population, divided by the number of samples less one. &#160;Its expected value (theoretical mean) is the </text><text style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt; font-style:italic; color:#000000;" translate="true">population variance</text><text style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt; color:#000000;" translate="true">. &#160;The square root of the sample variance is the </text><text style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt; font-style:italic; color:#000000;" translate="true">sample standard deviation</text><text style="font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt; color:#000000;" translate="true">.</text></para>
  </body>
